result.execSummary:
The defendant Marandrea S White was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Disorderly Conduct [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse - Infliction of Physical Pain or Injury], a class B misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 947.01(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Marandrea S White in court, in custody, with Attorney Samuel W. Benedict.   Kristi J Gordon appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count #3.  Court performs plea colloquy and finds Defendant guilty of Count #3.  Counts #1 & 2 are dismissed and read-in.  State gives sentencing recommendations.  Attorney Benedict makes statements regarding sentencing.  Defendant makes statements.  Court sentences the Defendant to the following:

COUNT #3:  IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

90 DAYS HUBER  (5 DAYS CREDIT, IF REVOKED)

TERM OF PROBATION:  1 YEAR       *CONSECUTIVE TO PRESENT SENTENCE*    **Transfer allowed to Milwaukee County**

CONDITIONS OF PROBATON:  
____Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
____Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
____No contact with: victim Allessundra B.

COSTS:  $343.00  (to be paid out of cash bail posted  and remainder is to be returned to poster)
DNA SURCHARGE:  WAIVED

**Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.**

**DEFENDANT TO BE RETURNED FORTHWITH**
